Detailed Description

cvmx_uahc::_ehci_usbintr

USBINTR = USB Interrupt Enable Register This register enables and disables reporting of the corresponding interrupt to the software. When a bit is set and the corresponding interrupt is active, an interrupt is generated to the host. Interrupt sources that are disabled in this register still appear in the USBSTS to allow the software to poll for events. Each interrupt enable bit description indicates whether it is dependent on the interrupt threshold mechanism. Note: for all enable register bits, 1= Enabled, 0= Disabled
